    <is_fda_regulated_device>No</is_fda_regulated_device>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study was designed as retrospective chart review to test our hypothesis whether there
      are the differences in inflammatory and anti-inflammatory mediators between asthmatic and
      ACOS patients with small airway obstruction, and COPD
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The data including spirometry, lung volume, impulse oscillometry, sputum data, demographic
      characters within 6 months are collected for later analysis. Sputum supernatants and
      cytospins are used to determine inflammatory and anti-inflammatory responses in those
      patients.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
